void setSerialableSubObjectsEnabled ( const ObjectIDVec &  valid_object_ids,
bool  recursive = false 
)

Set sub-object serialization enabled by object-id.

By default, sub-objects are serializeEnabled() and will be serialized.
Any attached sub-object with an id not in this vector will be setSerializeEnabled(false) preventing it from being serialized.

Parameters:
valid_object_ids List of object-ids to enable serialization for.
recursive whether to recurse into sub-object tree. Note that only valid objects are recursed into. If recursive is true then the only sub objects that will be serialized will be the objects that can be traversed with all object ids in valid_object_ids.
    1
   / \
  2   3
 /   / \
4   5   6
If this method is called on object marked as 1 and the vector of
objects ids is [3, 4]. Then objects 2 will be set false, object 4 will
be untouched, object 3 will be set true and obects 5 and 6 will be set false.
The only sub object serialized would be object 3.

Set whether or not the object will be serialized.
